The White House held a Principals Committee meeting to discuss a potential threat in or emanating from the Arabian Peninsula. The President instructed his National Security team to take appropriate steps to protect the American people. Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, Lisa Monaco, has been meeting with relevant members of the interagency throughout the week. National Security Advisor Susan Rice chaired the meeting, and attendees included White House Chief of Staff Denis McDonough, Secretary of State John Kerry, Secretary of Defense Chuck Hagel, and other high-ranking officials. The President has been receiving frequent briefings on the potential threat and preparedness measures.